data.name: Dear Diary,
data.loading_phrase: "Dear Diary," is the first track on POST HUMAN: SURVIVAL HORROR. It is set at the beginning of the apocalypse and takes reference to a video game, as most of the songs on the EP do. In the case of "Dear Diary,", there are multiple references to the original Resident Evil. Most specifically, the song alludes to a diary entry found in the Spencer mansion known as the "Keeper's Diary." The book is notable for its intimate description of a T-Virus infection written by a researcher undergoing the process. As the author succumbs to the infection, the last entry infamously reads: "Itchy. Tasty."

data.name: METALI!! (feat. Tom Morello)
data.loading_phrase: This is BABYMETAL's first single starring newest member Momoko! The chant "Wasshoi!", reoccurring along the song, is commonly associated with traditional Japanese festivals, known as "matsuri", where people carry large portable shrines called "mikoshi" through the streets. Participants in these festivals chant "Wasshoi" as they coordinate their movements to lift and carry the mikoshi.

data.name: Low
data.loading_phrase: Low is the second track (via digital streaming platforms) off Darkest Hour's fourth album, Undoing Ruin. Undoing Ruin has been regarded as one of the most influential metalcore albums of all time. It has also been debated as their magnum opus. Undoing Ruin was produced by metal legend Devin Townsend and was Darkest Hour's first album to reach the Billboard 200 albums chart debuting at 138
data.archivePath: Darkest Hour - Low

data.name: Two Alive Amongst the Dead
data.album: Two Alive Amongst the Dead - Single
data.loading_phrase: Two Alive Amongst the Dead is a standalone single from Better Lovers. Guitarist/producer Will Putney said “‘Two Alive…‘ was birthed on tour this Summer. We were having fun with the high energy, aggressive material live, and that cathartic spirit carried into this song. This is a band that never stops having ideas and likes the challenge of showing new music to fans live, so it was performed and fine-tuned on our Fall dates, and then immediately tracked in the studio between touring to make sure that fire stayed intact. There is no better feeling than capturing lightning in a bottle like this.” Greg Puciato added "This song is about saying fuck you to the societal and institutional pressure to fall for ‘me versus you’/’us versus them’ divisional tactics and realizing that we’re stronger when we remember the ways we’re the same, trying to find commonalities instead of differences. Understanding and finding compassion for one another instead of allowing ourselves to be separated and controlled. Brothers and sisters. Pieces of the same consciousness.”
data.driveFileName: Better Lovers - Two Alive Amongst the Dead.zip
data.archivePath: Better Lovers - Two Alive Amongst the Dead

data.name: Perpetual Terminal
data.loading_phrase: Perpetual Terminal is the first single, title track, and first song off Darkest Hour's tenth album. It is also the first song released from the band in nearly seven years. “This is a whole Darkest Hour album in one song,” the band says. “It felt like the perfect album opener, eventually became the title track, and therefore is the perfect place to start as we present this new album to the world. Lyrically, it touches on all of the themes of the record — an album centered around the duality of survival and rebirth. Or, you could just say, some new music from old friends who just won’t ever give up.”
data.archivePath: Darkest Hour - Perpetual Terminal
